HEADWORD: Purpurogenous
<hw>Pur`pu*rog"e*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>purpura</ets> purple + <ets>-genous</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having the power to produce a purple color;
<as>as, the <ex>purpurogenous</ex> membrane, or choroidal epithelium, of
the eye</as>. See <cref>Visual purple</cref>, under
<er>Visual</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purr</ent>⟦br⟧
